cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.CR

This paper deals with a large dataset of text posts from a specific board on 4chan, which makes it highly relevant to the natural language processing (NLP) community. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also includes a statistical analysis of the dataset, which involves data mining and machine learning techniques, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) possible sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses toxicity scores and named entities, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
